# AI Distraction Blocker — Architecture

## What It Does

A Manifest V3 Chrome extension that detects and blocks distracting websites during
configurable focus hours. Uses rule-based classification first, then falls back to an
AI API (Claude Sonnet 4.6 via unlimitedclaude.com) for ambiguous URLs. Tracks binge
usage per domain and escalates interventions from soft warnings to hard blocks.

---

## Project Structure

```
ai-distraction-blocker/
├── manifest.json              # MV3 extension config — declares permissions, scripts, icons
├── background/
│   └── worker.js              # Service worker — core classification + storage logic
├── content/
│   ├── content.js             # Injected into every page — renders overlays, tracks scrolling
│   └── overlay.css            # Styles for all in-page overlay UI
├── popup/
│   ├── popup.html             # Toolbar popup markup
│   ├── popup.js               # Popup logic — status, stats, quick actions
│   └── popup.css              # Popup styles
├── options/
│   ├── options.html           # Full settings page markup
│   ├── options.js             # Settings logic — 6 sections, charts, import/export
│   └── options.css            # Settings styles
└── icons/
    ├── icon16.png
    ├── icon48.png
    └── icon128.png
```

---

## Tech Stack

- Vanilla JS — no frameworks, no build step, runs directly in the browser
- Chrome Extensions API (Manifest V3)
  - chrome.storage.local     — persistent settings and stats
  - chrome.alarms            — minute-tick for stat tracking
  - chrome.notifications     — binge warnings
  - chrome.tabs / webNavigation — tab lifecycle and SPA navigation
- Web Audio API — alert sounds on overlay display
- External API — POST https://api.unlimitedclaude.com/v1/chat/completions
  - Model: claude-sonnet-4.6
  - Used only for ambiguous URLs that rule-based logic can't classify

---

## Entry Points

| File                  | Trigger                                              |
|-----------------------|------------------------------------------------------|
| background/worker.js  | Registered as service worker; starts on browser open |
| content/content.js    | Injected at document_idle on every page load         |
| popup/popup.html      | Opened when user clicks the extension icon           |
| options/options.html  | Opened via chrome.runtime.openOptionsPage()          |

---

## Component Breakdown

### background/worker.js — The Brain
Runs as a persistent service worker. Owns all decision logic and storage.

Key responsibilities:
- DEFAULTS / storage schema — initializes settings on first install
- Migration — converts legacy blockTime format to focusWindows array
- isInAnyFocusWindow()     — checks if current time is inside an enabled focus window
- isWhitelisted()          — matches hostname against user's whitelist
- ruleBasedClassify()      — hardcoded ~20 distracting domains; special YouTube logic:
                              homepage/shorts = distracting, /watch?v= = productive
- classifyWithAI()         — POSTs URL + title + meta + body excerpt to the AI API;
                              expects { classification, reason } back
- handlePageClassify()     — main decision pipeline (see Data Flow below)
- advanceStage()           — escalates intervention stage per tab (1 → 2 → 3)
- getBingeStatus()         — sliding window check: sums usage entries within windowHours
- recordBingeSeconds()     — appends timestamped usage entry for a domain
- adb-minute-tick alarm    — fires every 60s; increments distractingMinutes stat
                              for all currently-distracting tabs
- Tab cleanup              — clears per-tab state on tab close or navigation away

### content/content.js — The UI Layer
Injected into every page. Communicates with the worker via chrome.runtime.sendMessage.

Key responsibilities:
- classifyCurrentPage()    — sends CLASSIFY_PAGE with page metadata; calls showStage()
- showStage(stage)         — renders the correct overlay:
    Stage 0  no overlay (productive / whitelisted / outside hours)
    Stage 1  "Focus Check" — soft warning; Go Back / Snooze 5min / Allow Once / Continue
    Stage 2  "Last Warning" — same options, escalated tone
    Stage 3  Full-page hard block — dark screen, motivational quote, Leave button,
             live countdown timer if binge-blocked
- showCountdownBadge()     — floating SVG ring countdown (20s) between stage transitions
- showBingeIndicator()     — persistent bottom-left widget: domain usage bar + time left
- startBingeHeartbeat()    — sends BINGE_HEARTBEAT every 30s to record usage;
                             triggers stage 3 if binge limit is reached mid-session
- SPA navigation           — patches history.pushState/replaceState + popstate listener
                             to re-classify on client-side URL changes
- Doomscroll detection     — tracks scroll velocity; 10+ rapid bursts re-trigger classify
- Keyboard shortcut        — Escape dismisses stage 1/2 overlays

### popup/popup.js — Quick Actions
Shown when user clicks the toolbar icon.

Displays:
- Status badge: Blocking Active / Outside Hours / Paused / Site Blocked
- Today's stats: interventions, wasted minutes, exits
- Focus windows list with active/inactive indicators
- Binge usage bar for the current tab's domain
- Pause 30min / Resume toggle
- Whitelist current site button
- Link to full settings page

### options/options.js — Full Settings
6-section settings page with sidebar navigation.

Sections:
- Dashboard      — hero stats, focus score (% of interventions where user exited),
                   day streak, weekly bar chart, daily breakdown table
- Focus Windows  — add/edit/delete time windows (label, start, end, enabled toggle)
- Binge Guard    — add/edit/delete per-domain rules (limit in min/sec, rolling window hours);
                   shows live usage bar per rule
- Intervention   — choose mode: Soft Nudge / Hard Block / Escalating (default)
- Whitelist      — add/remove always-allowed domains
- API Key        — save UnlimitedClaude API key (stored locally, never sent elsewhere)

Also handles: export/import settings as JSON, reset stats, copy debug info.

---

## Data Flow

```
Page loads
  └─► content.js: classifyCurrentPage()
        └─► [CLASSIFY_PAGE msg] ──► worker.js: handlePageClassify()
                ├─ getBingeStatus()        → blocked?  → return stage 3
                ├─ allowedOnceTabs?        → allowed?  → return stage 0
                ├─ pauseUntil > now?       → paused?   → return stage 0
                ├─ isInAnyFocusWindow()    → outside?  → return stage 0
                ├─ isWhitelisted()         → listed?   → return stage 0
                ├─ ruleBasedClassify()     → productive → return stage 0
                │                         → distracting → return stage 1 (or 3 if hard mode)
                │                         → null (ambiguous)
                └─ classifyWithAI()        → productive → return stage 0
                                           → distracting → return stage 1 (or 3 if hard mode)
        └─► content.js: showStage(stage)
                ├─ stage 1: Focus Check overlay
                │     └─ "Continue" clicked → 20s countdown badge
                │           └─► [STAGE_ADVANCE] → worker returns stage 2
                ├─ stage 2: Last Warning overlay
                │     └─ "Continue" clicked → 20s countdown badge
                │           └─► [STAGE_ADVANCE] → worker returns stage 3
                └─ stage 3: Hard block (no escape unless binge countdown expires)

Every 30s while on a distracting page:
  content.js: [BINGE_HEARTBEAT] ──► worker.js: recordBingeSeconds()
                                          └─► getBingeStatus() → blocked? → push stage 3

Every 60s (chrome.alarms):
  worker.js: count tabs currently in distracting state → increment distractingMinutes stat
```

---

## Storage Schema (chrome.storage.local)

| Key              | Type     | Description                                              |
|------------------|----------|----------------------------------------------------------|
| apiKey           | string   | UnlimitedClaude API key (optional)                       |
| focusWindows     | array    | [{id, enabled, label, start, end}]                       |
| interventionMode | string   | "soft" / "hard" / "both" (escalating)                    |
| whitelist        | string[] | Always-allowed hostnames                                 |
| bingeRules       | array    | [{id, enabled, domain, limitSecs, windowHours}]          |
| bingeUsage       | object   | {domain: [{ts, secs}]} — rolling timestamped usage log   |
| stats            | object   | {"YYYY-MM-DD": {distractingMinutes, interventions, exited}} |
| pauseUntil       | number   | Unix ms timestamp; blocking disabled until this time     |
| _userConfigured  | bool     | Prevents overwriting user settings with defaults         |

---

## AI Classification

Only triggered when ruleBasedClassify() returns null (ambiguous URLs — e.g. YouTube
playlists, channels, search results, unknown domains).

Request:
  POST https://api.unlimitedclaude.com/v1/chat/completions
  Authorization: Bearer <apiKey>
  {
    model: "claude-sonnet-4.6",
    max_tokens: 100,
    system: "You are a productivity assistant...",
    messages: [{ role: "user", content: "<url> <title> <meta> <body excerpt>" }]
  }

Expected response:
  { classification: "productive" | "distracting", reason: "..." }

The extension works fully without an API key — AI classification is skipped and
ambiguous URLs are treated as productive (not blocked).

---

## Intervention Modes

| Mode                  | Behavior                                              |
|-----------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
| Soft Nudge            | Stage 1 only — easy to dismiss                        |
| Hard Block            | Jumps straight to stage 3 — no escape                 |
| Escalating (default)  | Stage 1 → 20s → Stage 2 → 20s → Stage 3              |

---

## Binge Guard

Tracks time spent on a domain within a rolling time window (e.g. 30 min in last 2 hours).
Usage is stored as timestamped entries in bingeUsage. On each BINGE_HEARTBEAT (every 30s),
entries older than windowHours are pruned and remaining seconds are summed. If the sum
exceeds limitSecs, the tab is hard-blocked with a countdown showing when the window resets.
